{
  "texts": [
    "The exploration of transformer models has gained traction due to their success in natural language processing (Tucudean et al. 2024).",
    "In this context, a mixed odor detection model for refrigerators was developed, leveraging the multi-head attention mechanism of the Transformer constrained on the Stiefel manifold to enhance attention weight stability and reliability (Sun et al. 2023).",
    "It also predicted odor concentration effectively, addressing key challenges in food spoilage detection.",
    "While transformer-based models offer improved attention mechanisms, they may still struggle with representing complex molecular structures in a chemically meaningful way.",
    "Traditional models often fail to capture subtle modulating behavior in chemical structures, leading to limited interpretability and accuracy."
  ]
}